.TH "vmw_cmd_res_switch_backup" 9 "vmw_cmd_res_switch_backup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_cmd_res_switch_backup \- Utility function to handle backup buffer switching
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_cmd_res_switch_backup
.BI "(struct vmw_private *dev_priv "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_sw_context *sw_context "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_resource *res "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *buf_id "  ","
.BI "unsigned long backup_offset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_priv" 12
Pointer to a device private struct.
.IP "sw_context" 12
The software context being used for this batch.
.IP "res" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "buf_id" 12
Pointer to the user-space backup buffer handle in the command
stream.
.IP "backup_offset" 12
Offset of backup into MOB.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function prepares for registering a switch of backup buffers in the
resource metadata just prior to unreserving. It's basically a wrapper around
vmw_cmd_res_switch_backup with a different interface.
